CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper October 23, 1965, pg. 3, reads: "Bean's Gulf Service - After - Here is the new Bean's Gulf Service Station, ready for its Grand Opening from Oct. 29 to Oct. 30.  To celebrate the opening, souvenirs and prizes will be given to lucky customers."
TitMainTitle: Herbert Bean's Gulf Station with car in center garage bay and mechanic standing in doorway, located at intersection of Centre Avenue and Kirkpatrick Street, near Humber Alley in Hill District
